WHO   — The Phones Ringing — the birth cry of a wired planet
WHAT  — The film's silliest image and truest prophecy: a planet wired into a single nervous system.
WHERE — LMM · The Lawnmower Man (1992)  Framework inputs: The Lawnmower Man (1992, dir. Brett Leonard, New Line); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because of all the futures the film imagined, this is the one that actually arrived.
HOW   — By staging ubiquitous connectivity as a god's announcement — and accidentally describing the world we now live in.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I was megalomaniac spectacle in 1992. Now every device really does light up at once. The joke was the prophecy: all the phones ring together now.

